            <span class="fq-ic" style="flex-shrink:0;width:26px;height:26px;border-radius:50%;background:#e2e2e2;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;transition:background .2s,transform .2s;" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M6 2v8M2 6h8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
          </button>
          <div class="fq-ans" style="display:none;padding:0 0 20px;font-size:0.93rem;color:#555;line-height:1.78;" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
            <div itemprop="text">Dark mode is now enabled by default on the majority of smartphones and a large share of desktop operating systems. When a subscriber views an email in dark mode, email clients like Apple Mail, Outlook on Windows, and Samsung Email can automatically invert or alter colors — making logos disappear, text unreadable, or designs look broken. Favze builds dark mode support into every email template using @prefers-color-scheme CSS, transparent PNG logos with fallbacks, dark-mode-aware background colors, and text contrast ratios that hold up in both light and dark environments.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

