          </button>
          <div class="fq-ans" style="display:none;padding:0 0 20px;font-size:0.93rem;color:#555;line-height:1.78;" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
            <div itemprop="text">Email deliverability refers to whether your emails actually reach subscribers' inboxes — as opposed to landing in spam, promotions tabs, or being blocked entirely. Favze improves deliverability by configuring SPF, DKIM, and DMARC authentication records; warming up new sending domains gradually; maintaining clean lists by removing hard bounces and unengaged contacts; monitoring sender reputation scores at Google Postmaster Tools and Microsoft SNDS; keeping spam complaint rates below critical thresholds; and optimizing content to avoid spam filter triggers. The result is consistently high inbox placement rates for Northern Indiana and Michiana businesses.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="fq-item" style="border-bottom:1.5px solid #ddd;" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <button class="fqb" type="button" aria-expanded="false" style="width:100%;background:none;border:none;text-align:left;padding:20px 0;font-weight:700;font-size:0.97rem;color:#0a0a0a;cursor:pointer;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:14px;font-family:var(--font-body);">
            <span itemprop="name">What is SPF, DKIM, and DMARC and why does Favze set these up for every client?</span>
            <span class="fq-ic" style="flex-shrink:0;width:26px;height:26px;border-radius:50%;background:#e2e2e2;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;transition:background .2s,transform .2s;" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M6 2v8M2 6h8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
          </button>
          <div class="fq-ans" style="display:none;padding:0 0 20px;font-size:0.93rem;color:#555;line-height:1.78;" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
            <div itemprop="text">SPF, DKIM, and DMARC are email authentication protocols that prove to receiving mail servers that your emails are legitimately sent from your domain. Without these records properly configured in your DNS settings, Gmail, Outlook, and Yahoo Mail will distrust your emails — sending them to spam or blocking them outright. In February 2024, Google and Yahoo began requiring SPF, DKIM, and DMARC for bulk senders. Favze audits and configures all three authentication records for every client's sending domain as part of email marketing setup, ensuring maximum inbox placement from the very first campaign send.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

